        "link": "https://www.france24.com/en/us-war-on-iran-tactically-very-successful-strategic-success-is-going-to-be-elusive",
        "orario": "18:23",
        "timestamp": 1773249822,
        "contenuto_esteso": "To display this content from YouTube, you must enable advertisement tracking and audience measurement. One of your browser extensions seems to be blocking the video player from loading. To watch this content, you may need to disable it on this site. 'US war on Iran tactically very successful: Strategic success is going to be elusive' Middle East Issued on: 11/03/2026 - 18:23 Genie Godula welcomes Daniel Schneiderman, Director of Global Policy Programs at Penn Washington. He argues that while the US has achieved significant tactical military successes in its campaign against Iran, the battlefield gains do not necessarily translate into victory. Washington’s stated objectives shift, day to day, from destroying Iran’s military and nuclear capabilities all the way to regime change. While Iran is focused on survival: the leadership can rebound and rebuild as long as Iran’s political system, military structure and economic foundations remain intact. 'King of the World' statue shows Trump with Epstein in \"Titanic\" recreation 11/03/2026 Americas G7 releases record amount of oil stocks to 'calm the markets down' 11/03/2026 Middle East Strait of Hormuz: US says it destroyed 16 Iranian mine-laying vessels 11/03/2026 Middle East Beirut: FRANCE 24 in the heart of the bombed southern suburbs 11/03/2026 Middle East Chile's first far-right president since Pinochet takes office 11/03/2026 Americas Volatile oil markets due to Middle East conflict increase jet fuel prices 11/03/2026 Middle East Trump a lot more concern about how war and oil prices will affect midterms 11/03/2026 Middle East Centre of Beirut shocked after Israeli army strikes apartment block 11/03/2026 Middle East UK deploys warship in the Mediterranean to protect British bases in Cyprus 11/03/2026 Middle East"
